Game.Title: Battletoads Double Dragon: The T.Bird Mission
Final Fight: The Last Raund Special

Game.Notes:
One of the best OpenBOR games around, very fun and very complete feel. There are 10 levels, 13 boss battles, great soundtrack, and even 3 secret characters!
What a great story from the OpenBoR community! Under the sharp and challenging title "A Tale of Vengeance" is a great beat 'em up game. This is not a remake, but a completely new game with a remixed desktop. Here, the characters of SNK and Capcom meet together in a team. The demon Shin has mastered almost all the warriors of the three sagas. This is the strongest form of Akuma, which has now taken over the human world. This creates a common story in which even the great Geese, the unlimited M. Bison, and the mystical Mr. Q are part of Demon Sheen's army.
However, several fighters, gathered in a group, set off. Ryo characters from Street Fighter, Samurai Maru, Kyo, Terry Bogard and Kim embark on a long journey through the depths of the Shin-controlled vacuum to drive him out of the human world.
Well, the game is quite interesting, although its dynamics can be difficult for anyone to master. Crowded with powerful fighters who are also quite fierce. Your characters, on the other hand, are quite slow and some of their tricks make them too vulnerable.
But these are almost two hours of intense play, where your gaming skills will be put to the test.
Game.Title: A Tale of Vengeance

Game.Notes: A four player feat em up created with OpenBOR, featuring Japan's three biggest Kaiju Heroes!
Game.Title: GUG: Godzilla: Ultraman: Gamera
Castlevania Dracula LCD Chronicles Deluxe Edition
Streets of Rage Z Return of the Hero

Game.Notes: In this version of Beats of Rage, you can play as the Dragon Ball Z character Super Sayan along with The Original Characters Mandy and Kula. It includes four modes of play with limited levels.
Game.Title: Beats of Rage: Alliance Super Sayan

Game.Notes: Thanos mounts the six Infinity Gems on his left glove to form the titular Infinity Gauntlet. Each Gem grants its bearer complete mastery over one aspect of the universe: Time, Space, Mind, Soul, Reality, and Power. Now all-powerful and desperate to win the affections of Death, Thanos decides to offer the entity a gift of love by completing a task she had given him, erasing half the sentient life in the universe (including most of the X-Men, Daredevil, and the Fantastic Four), quite literally with a snap of his fingers. The surviving heroes on Earth band together guided by the newly-resurrected Adam Warlock to battle Thanos. In a bid to impress Death, Thanos allows the heroes a slight chance of winning. Can you save the universe?
Game.Title: Marvel Super Heroes: War of the Gems

Game.Notes:
The year is 2044. After the events of World War I, the United States and the European Union no longer exist, were completely devastated by the nuclear invasion. The vacuum of power in North America gave rise to the Union of the Pacific, with Neopolis as the capital in South America.
While the world is still at peace, Neopolis police still fight crime in the city, even as they are getting more violent by the day.
They send the special agent, Isolde Shinwara, to investigate those cases that found traces of Drako, a drug that makes the person stronger and more aggressive. During the journey, Isolde will find that this will lead to a much more dangerous and corrupt path originally conceived...
Game.Title: Neon Lightning Force
Battletoads Double Dragon: Return of the Dark Forces

Game.Notes: Beats of Rage Remix is a BoR mod created by Mr.Q, it is based on the original Beats of Rage and contains new music, different stages and different characters.
Game.Title: Beats of Rage: Remix

Game.Notes:
Fighting Street is a Street Fighter remake, the first part of the famous fighting video game saga created and launched Capcom in 1987. In fact, the name of this miming comes from the conversion of the original game made for the Turbo Grafx CD.
In this case, it is not a fighting game but a beat'em up starring Ryu and Ken who tells the phase of his training with Master Gouken. Then, the game will change between pure beat'em phases against groups of enemies and levels in a single plan with much of the platforms. At certain times you will even have to fight some enemies in the usual style 1 vs. 1.
In fact, the main characters can use some of their classic movements such as Shoryuken or Hadoken. Although Fighting Street is based on the characters and situations of the first game, some characters from other games such as the Fight Final Saga also appears, so although most graphics are adapted from the original game, many of the audiovisual resources have been created right from the start.
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Fighting Street es un remake de Street Fighter, la primera parte de la famosa saga de videojuegos de lucha creada y lanzadapor Capcom en 1987. De hecho, el nombre de este fangame proviene de la conversin del juego original hecho para el Turbo Grafx CD.
En este caso, no se trata de un juego de lucha sino de un beat'em up protagonizado por Ryu y Ken que narra la fase de su entrenamiento con maestro Gouken. Entonces, el juego cambiar entre fases de beat'em puro contra grupos de enemigos y niveles en un solo planificar con gran parte de las plataformas. En ciertos momentos incluso tendrs que luchar contra algunos enemigos en el estilo habitual 1 vs 1.
De hecho, los personajes principales podrn utilizar algunos de sus movimientos clsicos como el Shoryuken o el Hadoken. Aunque Fighting Street se basa en los personajes y situaciones del primer juego, algunos personajes de otros juegos como de la saga Final Fight tambin aparece, as que aunque la mayora de los grficos estn adaptados del juego original, muchos de los recursos audiovisuales se han creado desde cero.
Game.Title: Fighting Street: Director's Cut

Game.Notes: Hyper Final Fight 3: Return of the Black is an OpenBOR beat 'em up created by Shin Azahara in 2015. Play as Haggar, Cody, Guy, Lucia, Mackie, Dean and Carlos, each of whom is equipped with a good set of special moves and combos.
Game.Title: Hyper Final Fight 3: Return of the Black

Game.Notes: Sega Brawlers Megamix brings together many of Sega's characters into one big beat 'em up! Created in OpenBOR, it features a roster of about 60 heroes from Sonic, Streets of Rage, Golden Axe, Guardian Heroes, and more. Special guest cameos include Earthworm Jim, the Battletoads, Rick Taylor from Splatterhouse, and lots of others!
Game.Title: Sega Brawlers MegaMix

Game.Notes:
Contra: Locked 'N' Loaded is a run-n-gun shooter developed as an attempt to remake the original Konami classic, Contra, using the OpenBOR engine. It features more playable characters and 3 missions, with two additional stages that can be unlocked upon completion. Some improvements include the ability to slide, shoot in 8 directions and carry two weapons.
Features:
12 different weapons Health bar which gives 3 hit points for player Health items Motorbike mode Lots of variety in the horizontal and vertical level design Challenging bosses and sub-bosses Save game enabled for all missions but Boss Rush
Game.Title: Contra: Locked 'N' Loaded

Game.Notes:
Beats of Rage Xtra is one of the games created by the Senile Team. Beats of Rage is the first game to start the OpenBoR saga, and Beats of Rage Xtra adds a new fresh atmosphere to this classic gameplay. The characters do not have a large set of super skills or combos. In this feature, this game is more like its classic counterparts from more than a quarter of a century ago. However, the plot is interest and intense enough, and the animation is at an excellent level.
To the main characters Max, Mandy in Kula, other attractive characters from the King of Fighters have now been added. These are the elegant Rock, Terry, whose fiery elements sweep the enemy from afar. Also participating are ninja May and boxer Evie.
The soundtrack to the game is reminiscent of the cult series Streets of Rage, whose remake is Beats of Rage.
Game.Title: Beats of Rage Xtra

Game.Notes:
Battletoads Double Dragon: The Revenge is a fan-made sequel to the 16-bit console hit from 1993, created using the OpenBOR engine and released in 2019 by MadGear.
Features:
Choose from 5 playable characters: Rash, Zitz, Pimple, Billy, & Jimmy Play solo and save Marian alone or play simultaneously for classic 2-player co-op action Follow the story as you go through 8 missions 3 vehicle stages to crank up the action 4 extra bonus modes selectable from the start Detailed old-school cutscenes between missions Lots of different moves to crush your enemies with Familiar enemies and bosses from both the Battletoads and Double Dragon series Soundtrack consisting of songs from various Battletoads and Double Dragon games And many other features!
Game.Title: Battletoads Double Dragon: The Revenge

Game.Notes: Count Monte: "I made a game on Mugen called Escape From The Psycho, which pretended to be the victim in a horror movie. You're being chased by a maniac, and you had to escape to the safe zone at the end of the level. In his way there was "lots of obstacles, slowing you down and allowing the maniac to catch up to you. I'm turning this game into Openbor, and changing the generic maniac to Michael Myers, so it's a Halloween game."
Game.Title: Halloween: The Wrath of Michael Myers

Game.Notes: 2 Alien races have clashed for years, the winner will be decided by the champion of each race Play as the champion of a race. Travel and shoot your way through different worlds and levels. Win your race and defeat the other champion!
Game.Title: Aliens Clash
Rescue Command Against the Amazon Girls
Beats of Rage: Rhythm of Destruction 1

Game.Notes:
It's the Bride's mission to cross Oren-Ishi off her revenge list after being left for dead on her wedding day, in this side-scrolling beat 'em up based on the hit film by Quentin Tarantino.
First created by the Senile Team in 2004, this old OpenBOR remake by Thatcher Productions adds extensive animations and fixed level designs, as well as new enemy A.I., character moves and other enhancements.
Game.Title: Kill Bill

Game.Notes: You accompany Astrix and Oblix in their adventures. The game is set up like the old school Batman Returns, or King of Dragons. You have an energy bar. Use your energy to perform two different attacks and beat the Roman army.
Game.Title: Asterix & Caesar's Challenge
Final Fight Vs The King Of Fighters: Episode 1
Super Street Fighter II Turbo HD Remix

Game.Notes: Play out classic RPGs, but this time you get full control. Talk to the towns folk, find a quest, and take down the monsters. Get the treasure, rinse and repeat. Simple and addictive gameplay will keep you coming back!
Game.Title: ClaFan: Classic Fantasy

Game.Notes:
Mortal Kombat: Outworld Assassins is a 2D beat 'em up developed by Magggas and modded by Gurtag using the OpenBOR engine. It was originally released in 2010 and updated eight years later.
Play solo or co-op as Sub-Zero, Scorpion or Noob Saibot and fight off countless enemies from Mortal Kombat lore using a lethal array of attacks and special moves, complete with the blood and guts the franchise is known for. Gameplay is fast and the controls are tight, responsive and so satisfying to send limbs flying and finish off foes with a decapitation.
On March 21, 2018, Magggas released a widescreen version of the game that includes bug fixes and minor tweaks to the original, known as Mortal Kombat: Outworld Assassins XL.
Game.Title: Mortal Kombat: Outworld Assassins
Beast and Blanka in the Violent World

Game.Notes:
Paying homage to the classic beat 'em up in the arcades, The Simpsons: Treehouse of Horror stars Homer, Bart, and Krusty as they try to stop an alien invasion from taking over the Earth. The game plays just like the original arcade version, featuring lots of characters and bosses -- including Futurama and Family Guy cameos -- as well as exciting levels, cool weapons, and vehicles to drive!
Includes Bonus Games! - Reclaim Burns Manor: Play as Vampire Mr. Burns and stop the criminals from looting your mansion - Tournament mode: Face enemies in one-on-one combat - Family Guy: You are Peter and see the events that unfold before he and his family are teleported to Springfield
Game.Title: Simpsons Treehouse of Horror

Game.Notes:
Battle your way over land, sea and air down into the depths of Cobra Island, in an attempt to stop a doomsday missile from being launched by Cobra Commander!
G.I. Joe: Attack on Cobra Island is an OpenBOR beat 'em up starring everyone's favorite Joes, such as Snake Eyes, Duke, and unlockables like Hawk and Sgt. Slaughter, with several missions, updated sprites, new enemies and more!
Game.Title: G.I. Joe: Attack on Cobra Island

Game.Notes:
Evil is on the rise, and it's up to the World Heroes to save the day! World Heroes Supreme Justice Extra is a widescreen update to the Neo Geo arcade original from 1992. It was created by Magggas using the OpenBor engine in 2013 and officially completed five years later.
This remake features 11 fighters, including 6 new ones: Muscle, J. Max, Janne, Gokuu, Kisarah, and C. Kidd. Along with fast and fluid controls, each character can pull off serial combos and unique super moves. Beat 'em up and smash your way across the stages to find health, money and weapons, with a tough boss waiting at the end. With great gameplay and HD visuals, it's a perfect example of a classic made modern.
Game.Title: World Heroes Supreme Justice Extra

Game.Notes: Pierwolf presents its project using the OpenBor engine, but this time it will not be a street fighting game, but the classic recreational game called Dungoons & Dragons. This trained game is very entertaining and addictive as when it came out at the time... ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- Pierwolf presenta su proyecto utilizando el motor OpenBOR, pero esta vez no ser un juego de lucha callejera, sino el clsico juego recreativo llamado Dungeons & Dragons. Este juego entrenado es muy entretenido y adictivo como cuando sali en su momento...
Game.Title: Dungeons & Dragons: Knights & Dragons
Bruce Lee: Revenge of the Dragon

Game.Notes:
Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles - The Wrath of Shredder is a mud of the ninja turtles created by Bonusjz using OpenBor. Most graphics have been extracted from other TMNT games. It is the first TMNT game that contains blood.
This game is modified by Ripfire in its Alpha version since it was created by an old OpenBor engine which may contain errors either graphics or code interpretation in this Beta Version of the Dreambor.
Game.Title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: The Wrath of Shredder (Special Edition)

Game.Notes: Dragon Ball Z: Attack of the Saiyans is an OpenBOR beat 'em up released in 2017. The game tells the story of Goku's father, Bardock, and of the final days in the life of planet Vegeta. With sharp graphics and cutscenes, fast gameplay and responsive controls, the game is a well-polished entry into the OpenBOR library.
Game.Title: Dragon Ball Z: Attack of the Saiyans

Game.Notes:
Marvel Infinity War is a fan-made game using the OpenBor engine. This beat 'em up hearkens back to the arcades of old, with 85 playable good guys and bad guys from the Marvel universe. Using a six-button control scheme, each character has a special move and an ultra move, along with special assist characters to summon during the heat of battle.
There are five different overarching teams of characters available, including the Avengers, X-Men, Cosmic, Street Level, and Villains. They each visit their own stages and battle different bosses.
Game.Title: Marvel Infinity War
Rescue Command Arrange: Ep. 1: Escaping from Bad Girls Island 2.5D

Game.Notes: Chrono Killer is based on the SNES classic, Chrono Trigger, and reuses sprites and locations to create a beat em up. It also has some guest characters including Link, Trunks, and Samurai Jack.
Game.Title: Chrono Killer
Vermilion Sword: The Legend of Calibur

Game.Notes: Elijah Simon: "OVERLOAD: The Game (based on the original animated series), available October 30, 2011! Now you can play as Ace & Remy in an epic adventure. I hope everyone enjoys this. This is the third video game that I have created. In the past I have made Skull Kingz and Skull Kingz: The Remake. I am very proud of myself for making this. I also play it faithfully every day on my X-Box. lol :P''
Game.Title: Overload

Game.Notes:
The Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and Battletoads together in a very fun game for one or two players created by Brazileo kmilloz. The gameplay is similar to the old recreational games of the T.M.N.T., but with new attacks and special movements, in addition to including legendary Battletoads. The difficulty of the game is an authentic hell, but it is relieved playing multiplayer, but if you want to test your Skills playing alone, if you dare ...
TMNT & Battletoads juntos en un juego muy divertido para uno o dos jugadores creado por el brazileo Kmilloz. La jugabilidad es similar a los antiguos juegos de recreativas de los T.M.N.T., pero con nuevos ataques y movimientos especiales ademas de incluir a los legendarios BattleToads.La dificultad del juego es un autentico infierno pero se alivia jugando multijugador, pero si quieres poner a prueba tus habilidades jugando solo, si te atrevez...
Game.Title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and BattleToads (Special Edition)

Game.Notes: Earth's Champion Tobias Blakewell is missing and the remaining Omni-Masters have departed in search of the Relic Master whom now has possession of the all powerful Stone of David. In their absence, the Prince of Darkness has taken over and resurrected ever evil being to have ever walked the Earth. In this great time of darkness 3 heroes have stepped forth Dante, Kolchak the Night stalker, and a blind priest named Gibson Praise... The Countdown to Oblivion has begun...
Game.Title: Crisis Evil: Countdown to Oblivion

Game.Notes:
Fighters History: Revenge's developed by Pierwolf, Dupu and Ripfire with new characters, scenarios and many improvements and compatibility. The inclusion of new characters and scenarios that we could only dream of make it a fun game that you can try for free.
This fan game makes possible something like a remake of the game with which it is possible to spend hours of fun thanks to the OpenBor engine.
Game.Title: Fighters History: Revenge (Remix Edition)

Game.Notes:
Night Slashers X is a fan-made beat 'em up based on the Data East arcade classic Night Slashers, which sees four playable monster hunters fighting their way through hordes of the undead.
Created in OpenBOR, the game features upgraded visuals, a widescreen mode and more enemies. The three original playable characters are present, each with their own unique move-sets, and now theyre joined by Ash from The Evil Dead. Ash cant pick up and use weapons but he keeps the monsters at bay with his deadly boomstick and trademark arm-mounted chainsaw!
With only 2 continues per playthrough, Night Slashers X is a tough game. Play with up to four players to aid your chances in this pixel-perfect retro throwback!
Game.Title: Night Slashers X

Game.Notes: The man of your dreams is back and this time in, full on, 16-bit glory. Fight through an army of Freddy's past victims, hellish nightmares, and Krueger himself as one of the Dream Warriors. Do you have what it takes?
Game.Title: Dreams of Rage

Game.Notes:
Hyper Duel is a Japanese video game developed by Technosoft and released in 1993. It is a horizontally scrolling shooter which takes inspiration from the Thunder Force series. The game has the player take control of a ship that can transform between a humanoid mecha and a space ship. The game was released in arcades in 1993, running on the TEC442-A hardware, then was ported to the Sega Saturn in 1996. It has never been released...
BonusJZ takes up the concept and transfers it to the OpenBOR engine but with a big difference, between this you cannot transform the ships into a humanoid wick and only the levels are a compilation of other Matamarcians...
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Hyper Duel es un videojuego japons desarrollado por Technosoft y lanzado en 1993 en Recreativas y luego fue portado a Sega Saturn en 1996. Es un juego de disparos de desplazamiento horizontal que se inspira en la serie Thunder Force, hace que el jugador tome el control de una nave que puede transformarse entre un mecha humanoide y una nave espacial.
BonusJZ retoma el concepto y lo traslada al motor OpenBOR pero con grandes diferencia, entre esto no se puede transformar las naves en mecha humanoide y solo los niveles son una compilacin de otros matamarcianos...
Source / Fuente : https://segaxtreme.net/threads/hyper-duel-first-true-openbor-shump.16302/
Game.Title: Hyper Duel: First True Shmup

Game.Notes: Inspired in the game of GBA
Game.Title: Dragon Ball
Super Final Fight Gold Plus LNS

Game.Notes: Golden Axe Genesis is a fan-made sequel to the arcade beat 'em ups from the 90's, featuring new enemies, graphics, faster gameplay and an overhaul to the balance and design. Developed by SEEP, a two-man team of brothers from Italy, it was made using the OpenBOR engine and offers 13 playable heroes and numerous villains to battle from the franchise's saga. There's a Story mode and a survival mini-game called Duel mode, as well as the ability to play the arcade original with the new characters and updates.
Game.Title: Golden Axe Genesis

Game.Notes:
Battletoads in BattleWorld Openbor developed by non-profit fans and with new characters, scenarios and many improvements and compatibility. The inclusion of new characters and scenarios that we could only dream of make it a fun game that you can try for free.
This fan game makes possible something like a remake of the game, with which it is possible to spend hours of fun thanks to the OpenBor graphics engine.
Game.Title: Battletoads in BattleWorld

Game.Notes: Evil Dead is a side-scrolling beat 'em up using OpenBOR, created by Thatcher Productions in 2021. Control Ash as he hacks and slashes his way through deadites galore. Developer Andrew Thatcher explained that this was the first game he ever made, and called the November 2021 update the "definitive redux version", overhauling the original.
Game.Title: Evil Dead
Street Fighter Beats of Rage Remix II

Game.Notes:
You know the score. The Shadow Warriors decided it's a good idea to kidnap Marion. Show them just what a mistake they made! As Billy or Jimmy, you have all the classic Double Dragon moves at your disposal. Bring Marion back safely, but watch out - more missions await you.
The Reloaded Version is for Sega DreamCast ...
Game.Title: Double Dragon Gold (Reloaded Version)
Bare Knuckle III: Yesterday Once More

Game.Notes: Final Fight X is probably the most conservative of Final Fight versions of OpenBOR, being much more faithful to Capcom's original work, so much so that we could almost consider it as the real Final Fight 2 instead of the game that was released for Super Nintendo. In Final Fight X you are able to choose between the three protagonists that appeared in the original game (Haggar, Guy and Cody) to overcome the different stages, in which they will face against all the enemies that appeared in the original title. Both graphically and playability, the game is a carbon copy of the original arcade, but with completely new stages.
Game.Title: Final Fight X
Super Smash Wars: Sega vs. Nintendo
Street Fighter Rage World Olympic Tour

Game.Notes:
Ripfire: ''Bloodbane presents its new project using the OpenBOR engine, but this time it will not be a street fighting game, but rather, a Shoot'Em Up called Rainbow, a simple but very entertaining game ... Rainbow: DreamCast Edition is exclusively for Sega DreamCast, I've Re-edited some concept of the author.''
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ripfire: ''Bloodbane nos presenta su nuevo proyecto usando el motor de OpenBOR, pero esta vez no sera un juego de pelea callejera, sino mas bien, un matamarciano llamado Rainbow, un juego sencillo pero muy entretenido... Rainbow: DreamCast Edition es exclusivamente para Sega DreamCast, he re-editados algunos concepto del autor...."
Game.Title: Rainbow

Game.Notes:
This Bare Knuckle Vacuum is a fan-made Streets of Rage based free MOD game designed by Chinese fan players Anking and Volcanic, with fresh originality and crafty designs.
-Key Features- 7 characters (1 hidden but selectable directly) Excellent fighting systems with combos Long levels Many bosses New and cool moves for each character Usable improvised weapons R.E.D. system similar to the magical attack in classic Golden Axe The ability to use guns 4-player support
Game.Title: Bare Knuckle VACUUM

Game.Notes: The Japanese author, Shin, has seen fit to revisit the Guardians / Denjin Makai saga of Banpresto calling as protagonists some characters seen in that of Street Fighter Zero. The result is a fun scrolling fighting game where we can go around the streets with Ryu, Cody, Sagat (and not only) to break a little bit of everything that moves (and of course also what doesn't move, as always).
Game.Title: Denjin Makai ZERO

Game.Notes:
He-Man and the Masters of the Universe is a side-scrolling brawler featuring He-Man, She-Ra and pals battling their way through Eternia to defeat the evil Hordak. Created in the OpenBOR engine, up to four players hack and slash through 28 levels of arcade fun based on the classic 80's cartoon.
Hordak has invaded Eternia, banished Skeletor and Evil-Lyn from Snake Mountain, and plans to steal the Diamonds of Power. To stop him, choose from a sizeable roster of playable characters, like Man-at-Arms, Orko, Sorceress, Teela, Skeletor, Evil-Lyn, Ram-Man, or even the Thundercats' Lion-O. Each character has their own special moves like flying or summoning the big cats, BattleCat and Panthor.
There's a Story mode and Versus mode, with a nice variety to the level design, mixing in platforming and shooter stages with ally protection, mazes and time-limited gameplay. Along the way, the heroes will encounter boss fights against some of the most memorable villains from the series, including fan favorites Beast Man, Mer-Man and Trap Jaw, among many others.
Game.Title: He-Man and the Masters of the Universe

Game.Notes:
Start an epic journey in a land full of mystery and adventure! Explore the realm of Karameikos, complete the quests scattered across the map, find new friends that will join in your travels, and unveil the mystery under the monsters' invasion!
New & improved level-up system! as you level up, you will gain health points, magic points and new exciting special moves for all the characters! New game modes! Unlock the Endless Quest with all the characters available from the start! Or put yourself to the test with the new Arcade Quests, where you start at level 20 from the beginning, and face all the quests without break, in a classic arcade battle that will leave you breathless! New block system! Now you have an appropriate button to defend yourself! New recover system! When knocked down, press the jump button and the directional controls repeatedly to stand up immediately and crush your enemies! up to 4 players can play together! Can you survive in this perilous lands by yourself, or you'll face the threats with your trusted fellowship? tons of treasures, monsters and DRAGONS!
Knights and Dragons: The Endless Quest is a beat 'em up in the style of old tabletop games. Thanks to the OpenBor engine and tons of material taken directly from old Dungeons and Dragons titles, it provides as close to a classic role-playing game experience as you can get.
Players can choose between various classes of characters: warrior, cleric, mage, archer, dwarf, and thief. One to four players can participate using Xbox 360 controllers and the keyboard.
Once you've chosen your characters, the adventure begins. Your characters start with a very limited amount of life points, which you can increase as you gain levels. So be careful, because at the start of the adventure, your characters can die after just one or two hits.
Just like in Dungeons and Dragons, you can choose which missions you want to play. There are lots of different options, and each will reward you handsomely if you are able to complete it. Of course, if all of your characters die, it's game over.
Once you finish Knights and Dragons, you'll gain access to additional playing modes, with all the characters unlocked and a few extra surprises.
Knights and Dragons: The Endless Quest is one of the best beat 'em ups based in the Dungeons and Dragons franchise that you'll find. It offers a dozen hours of classic action, difficult enough to provide a real challenge.
Game.Title: Knights & Dragons: The Endless Quest

Game.Notes: NelsonComica is one of the earlier OpenBOR efforts, and the very first known to utilize digitized assets. Although a mechanical reskin, the game remains an interesting bit of history for its at the time new graphical approach in an OpenBOR v2.XXX project.
Game.Title: Nelsoncomica
Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles III The Manhattan Project

Game.Notes:
Ryuko No Ken Nekketsu (the Japanese name for 'Art of Fighting') is a 'beat 'em up' inspired by Nintendo's legendary River City Ransom. Here, you can choose from various characters to hit the dangerous streets of Japan and take down the gangs and other city scum.
Ryuko No Ken Nekketsu provides you with more than a dozen different characters, depending on the playing mode you choose. There is classic arcade mode, but also some additional options for you to show off your fighting skills.
Some of the available characters include, of course, Robert Garcia and Ryo Sakazaki from 'Art of Fighting', among others.
As you play, you can explore many different streets with vastly different styles. That's where you'll find more weapons and healing objects, which will be necessary to fight the game's different final bosses, who are way harder than the normal enemies.
Ryuko No Ken Nekketsu is a 2D action game that maintains the 'brawler' spirit from late 80s/early 90s games. And its graphics, directly inspired by the same games, are truly a delight.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ryuko No Ken Nekketsu (el nombre japons de "Art of Fighting") es un "beat" em up" inspirado en el legendario River City Ransom de Nintendo. Aqu, puedes elegir entre varios personajes para recorrer las peligrosas calles de Japn y acabar con las pandillas y la escoria de la ciudad.
Ryuko No Ken Nekketsu te proporciona ms de una docena de personajes diferentes, segn el modo de juego que elijas. Hay un modo arcade clsico, pero tambin algunas opciones adicionales para que muestres tus habilidades de lucha.
Algunos de los personajes disponibles incluyen, por supuesto, a Robert Garca y Ryo Sakazaki de 'Art of Fighting', entre otros.
Mientras juegas, puedes explorar muchas calles diferentes con estilos muy diferentes. Ah es donde encontrars ms armas y objetos curativos, que sern necesarios para luchar contra los diferentes jefes finales del juego, que son mucho ms duros que los enemigos normales.
Ryuko No Ken Nekketsu es un juego de accin en 2D que mantiene el espritu de "lucha" de los juegos de finales de los 80 y principios de los 90. Y sus grficos, directamente inspirados en los mismos juegos, son una autntica delicia.
Game.Title: Ryuko No Ken Nekketsu: Arrange Edition

Game.Notes:
This project is to pay tribute to the famous character created the genius of Shigeru Miyamoto, S.E.E.P. He decided to follow his own way by mixing the genre with the platform with the Beat Em Up, the result is: Mario Super Brawl.
Este proyecto es para rendir homenaje al famoso personaje creado el genio de Shigeru Miyamoto, S.E.E.P. decidi seguir su propio camino al mezclar el gnero con la Plataforma con el Beat Em Up, el resultado es: Mario Super Brawl.
Game.Title: Super Mario Brawl

Game.Notes: Battletoads Double Dragon IV: Return of The Dark Forces is a street fighting game, based on the Battletoads sagas from Tradewest and Double Dragon from Technos. The Toads from Battletoads and the brothers Billy and Jimmy from Double Dragon have returned, and once again they must hit the streets, beating everyone who gets in their way. This time, the characters of both games decide to meet to find out who is behind some explosions that affected the city and innocent people who had to flee their homes in search of refuge. During this period, enemies began to appear everywhere, turning the city into complete chaos. This is where frogs and humans unite to defend the population, using all their abilities and special moves to destroy this new threat.
Game.Title: Battletoads & Double Dragon IV: The Return of the Dark Forces
Street Fighter Vs The King of Fighters

Game.Notes: A 2d Adventure Beat'em up game. Help Norimaru, a simple student, to escape from Bullying on the school! Use Terry and the Vampire Arcueid to destroy all demons.
Game.Title: Bad School Girls

Game.Notes: Maximum Carnage Returns is an OpenBOR beat 'em up created by Silas Elrick Heat and Heat Games in 2017. This fan-made reboot of the 16-bit classic from 1994, Maximum Carnage, features three playable characters: Spider-Man, Deadpool and Venom.
Game.Title: Maximum Carnage Returns

Game.Notes: A tribute to 90s arcade brawlers, Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Shell Shocked was created with the OpenBOR engine by White Dragon Software and released in 2014. Play solo or co-op with up to 4 players, and choose from 11 characters to fight with, including the four ninja heroes and even villains like Bebop, Rocksteady and Foot Clan soldiers. There's nearly a dozen stages to fight through, with well-crafted cutscenes to advance the story. Overall, the game plays just like the 1989 arcade original, adding a few more special moves and upgrades for a great, new adventure.
Game.Title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Shell Shocked

Game.Notes: Mortal Kombat classic games, reimagined like a 16-bits beat 'em up.
Game.Title: Mortal Kombat: Defenders of the Realm
Rhythm of Destruction 2: Street Fighter Edition

Game.Notes: Open BOR mod, based on the characters from the Brazilian TV Show Chaves that aired for seven seasons in the 1970"s.
Game.Title: Chaves Streets

Game.Notes:
Comic book lovers rejoice. You can now play with all your favorite heroes and villains from many different publishers. It would take hours to try all the characters provided for this game. The technical implementation is in a classic style. It calls the familiar core of the game Beats of Rage, but some improvements have been added. You can now produce more combined attacks. All artistic components and cinematics, however, have been changed in detail to fully match the game.
New and attractive gameplay, often chaotic. There are many enemies, and it will be difficult for you to handle them all. However, the OpenBoR menu also offers the opportunity to get an unlimited number of credits. This will make it much easier for you.
The plot is very interesting, and for your characters you will use those of Marvel, including Batman, several versions of Captain America, the terrible Agony, Electro, several versions of Iron Man, Green Lantern, and the alien Manta. The set includes 27 different characters, and to the delight of users, it seems that in the future will be provided and more interesting new models to add to the current gameplay.
Game.Title: City of Heroes

Game.Notes:
Double Dragon Revolution Gaiden X is a game compilation designed for the OpenBOR engine created by the Chilean Gabo-Hanzo. This release is exclusive to Sega DreamCast and contains the following games: Double Dragon Revolution 1, Double Dragon Revolution 2 and Double Dragon Gaiden.
Double Dragon Revolution Gaiden X es una compilacin de juegos deseado para el motor OpenBOR creado por el chileno Gabo-Hanzo. Este lanzamiento es exclusivo para Sega DreamCast y contiene los siguientes juegos: Double Dragon Revolution 1, Double Dragon Revolution 2 y Double Dragon Gaiden.
Sources: Double Dragon Revolution 1: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EH7CMwuSDu0 Double Dragon Revolution 2: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tHyF9npC0pw Double Dragon Revolution 3 (AKA Gaiden): https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=woUHQ_JA0SQ
Game.Title: Double Dragon Revolution Gaiden X

Game.Notes:
Die_In_Fire: "Some of you already know about this, I'm working on a prequel of RCR.
I'm putting a lot of work on the gameplay on this one, I'm correcting some mistakes done on Valdivia City Ransom, and before you ask, VCR is not dead, but I got confused when I lost lot of stuff when I left my country, as it is going to have multiple paths etc, so I thought I needed a new refreshment.
Here's a little gameplay video, it is rough, but things like the black nonexistent border will be corrected, the enemies will be modified 100% too. and I have TONS of ideas that I want to fulfill, and I think everyone will be surprised, for now don't want to spill everything.
The history is that you use Kunio and Sugata to battle school bullies and the bosses from Nekketsu Kouha Kunio-kun.
Also I did some pictures, like this one I did from scratch..., so far I finished 3 weapons: iron stick, chain and knuckle, still have 7 more to go...
after that I will start working on stages and enemies, and finally Sugata.
cheers!!"
Game.Title: Valdivia City Ransom

Game.Notes:
A new enemy has summoned evil and killed all of the heroes! Discover the world of Greyhawk and stop Iuz's campaign to conquer the Kingdom of Furyondy! Undertake daring missions to rescue allies, sabotage enemy strongholds and find the secret to defeating this threat once and for all!
Created by Counte Monte on the OpenBOR engine, Dungeons and Dragons: The Rise of Warduke is not just a button-mashing beat 'em up but mixes in a bit of role-playing adventure as you visit towns across the map, talk to NPC's and fight random encounters. There are 13 playable characters, some of whom must be unlocked like dark elves and necromancers, who can learn dozens of spells, buy weapons and equipment, complete quests, hire mercenaries, solve puzzles and traps, find secret dungeons, joust for prizes, and much more!
Game.Title: Dungeons & Dragons: Rise of Warduke

Game.Notes: A fanmade OpenBor version of the CAPCOM arcade classic.
Game.Title: Darkstalkers

Game.Notes: With the added improvements, all the flaws are removed and you play a cleaner version where the battles are fought with ease. Bios meat screens have also been improved, which now give you more accurate information about your character's condition.Gilius Thunderhead, Ax Butler and Tyris Flare, will be your heroes. They are the fighters of the original game and here their skills are significantly improved.
Game.Title: Golden Axe Remake: Special Edition
Metal Gear Origin: Code Name-Solid Snake

Game.Notes:
Power Rangers: Beats of Power is a freeware fan-made indie developed arcade beat 'em up game created by Merso X Games on GameJolt. It was released online in 2014 and is available for Mac or PC.
The game is designed as a retro throwback to classic 1990s Power Rangers games, such as the Mighty Morphin Power Rangers games for the SNES and the Genesis and Power Rangers: The Fighting Edition. In March 2017, the game was updated with a Special Edition version released.
The game benefits greatly from the energetic tunes of the TV show. Also included are numerous voice clips and sound effects taken from the show.
Game.Title: Power Rangers: Beats of Power

Game.Notes:
Final Fight Gold: Super Extra is the latest known version by Ripfire of the Super Final Fight Gold Plus series by Pierwolf with Don Drago, FinalFighter and Ripfire. The game combines the best of Street Fighter and Final Fight with a gritty aesthetic and Pierwolf's trademark level.
More Info.: https://www.keeplinks.org/p100/63e01c1928ec5
Game.Title: Final Fight GOLD: Super Extra

Game.Notes:
Red Skull and Hydra are trying to take over the world! Grab up to four players and team up as one of dozens of Marvel's most powerful superheroes to stop them, in Marvel First Alliance 2.
This 16-bit beat 'em up was released in 2014 by ZVitor, a popular designer from Brazil who created the game using the OpenBor engine project. It features dozens of playable characters that are unlocked after each level in the Story mode. Finish the game and unlock numerous other modes, like a Spider-Man and Carnage scenario, X-Men and Apocalypse, or harder difficulties. The game plays like the traditional side-scrolling brawlers from the arcades with unique special abilities and power-ups, and adds some modern updates to the mix, like NPC-controlled heroes joining you during the fight and situation-specific characters available according to the story.
Game.Title: Marvel First Alliance 2

Game.Notes: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Rescue-Palooza is a fan-made beat 'em up using OpenBOR and created as an update and homage to the classic NES titles. It includes 4-player local co-op with 60 playable characters, more than 20 stages and bonus levels, as well as rideable vehicles. It also features improved graphics, voice clips from the cartoon show and countless references to the toy line, comics and culture. Cowabunga!
Game.Title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Rescue-Palooza!

Game.Notes:
Art of Fighting Trouble in South Town is a free game made by one person (jonsilva). It uses the OpenBor Engine, a free beat em up game engine.
- The game is similar to final fight or streets of rage series. - It contains several levels like fighting / bonus stages / interactive levels... - It uses edited characters from King of Fighters and other arcade games. - It has several animated GIFs/movies that will show at the end of each boss/ sequence of levels that will take you throw the story. - Approximately 15/20 hours of gameplay if you play very fast. - And much more.
Game.Title: Art of Fighting: Trouble in Southtown
Mega Man The Power War Ep. 1

Game.Notes:
Justice League United is an awesome old school side scrolling arcade beat em up that sees Batman, Wonder Woman and their super pals teaming up against DCs deadliest super villains.
Justice League United is a fantastic fan made project created in the OpenBOR engine that delivers a fun blend of shoot em up and beat em up Justice League arcade action. It features local co-op play across seven large stages with seven playable characters and lots of supervillains to beat up.
Gameplay is split up into three distinct styles of game modes 2D side scrolling beat em up action akin to the Batman and Robocop arcade games, Streets of Rage style 2.5D beat em up action and side scrolling shoot em up sections with vehicles. Its a nice mixture of game styles that adds a nice bit of variety and stops the gameplay from becoming too stale.
You can choose to play as Superman, Batman, Aquaman, Wonder Woman, Green Lantern, Cyborg and Flash. Each level of the game is based on the story and setting of each character, and all the characters have their strengths and own selection of cool special moves. Its a pretty tough game with some challenging boss fights, and you only have a finite number of continues, so you will need to use a bit of skill to make it to the end.
Justice League United really impresses with its high level of polish, fan service, quality of character animation, variety of gameplay and old school side scrolling arcade action.
Game.Title: Justice League United

Game.Notes: Megaman: War of the Past has the unique distinction of being the first fully completed Beats of Rage mod. Created by DCSteve in 2004, the mod displayed many features which would lead the way for even more enhancements to the original game module. The mod also influenced the further development of the Beats of Rage game engine, which eventually became OpenBoR.
Game.Title: Megaman: War of the Past

Game.Notes:
Double Dragon Reloaded: Alternate is a mix of the first two games in the Double Dragon saga, created with the OpenBOR project and released in 2017. It includes a roster of new characters along with old favorites, including wrestling legends like Hulk Hogan.
Up to two players can play together and the gameplay stays true to its predecessors with punch & kick attacks, grabs, weapons, and more. There are five game modes of beat 'em up fun, for example, a stage where you hunt down Andre the Giant after he destroys your motorcycle. The game takes all the best elements from the arcade classics while staying true to their spirit.
Game.Title: Double Dragon Reloaded: Alternate Edition

Game.Notes: Art of Fighting is originally a Versus fighting game that transforms here into Beat'em Up. All to offer us a story rich in twists and turns. All enriched with graphics of impeccable quality with characters taken directly from another SNK masterpiece, King of Fighters. Ryo Sakazaki learns that his father, Takuma, has disappeared and is believed to have been killed. As well as his sister, Yuri, who was also kidnapped. So he contacts his faithful friend Robert Garcia, and they go to the streets of South Town in search of them... The longevity of the game is excellent with a high level of difficulty (sometimes too exaggerated considering the few credits we have), several special moves for each character, two game modes and many secrets (including additional characters and levels) to unlock.
Game.Title: Art of Fighting: Beats of Rage Remix III

Game.Notes:
Golden Axe: The Curse of Death Adder is a fangame based on the classic fighting game Golden Axe developed in the OpenBOR engine.
With graphics ripped from several games in the franchise and, along with the gameplay, fun, sounds and music, you get the impression that you're playing an original Golden Axe from the arcade with more elements and difficulty. It also features sounds and snippets of music from Conan movies. In addition, you can play multiplayer and has three game modes.
Game.Title: Golden Axe: The Curse of Death Adder
Super Thundercats: The Lost Eye of Thundera

Game.Notes: Retro Gamer Adventure is an OpenBOR beat 'em up released in 2019 by Brazilian creator ZVitor. Similar in style to River City Ransom, it features 15 real-life playable characters from YouTube's gaming community with fully-voiced story sequences in Portuguese. Each character has a special move and costume set that takes inspiration from comics and video game culture. For example, ZVitor himself is playable and has the ability to blast enemies with an infinity stone gauntlet on his hand, donning an Aquaman suit when his power-up meter fills up. The game has great graphics and charming level design, with lots of fun characters to brawl with and against.
Game.Title: Retro Gamer Adventure
Splatterhouse I. Deception of the Mask
Final Fight meets Comics Zone and Battletoads

Game.Notes:
What do you want in a Streets of Rage title? Tight game play? Stiff challenge? All the original playable characters? Streets of Rage 2X takes all of this and adds much more to build a game that's all its own, yet still has the familiar Streets of Rage feel.
Best be ready though, bring anything less than your A game and this offering will spit you out like Bongo's last meal.
Four player support. Block, evade, juggle, and many other new techniques, all blended perfectly into the original move set. Unleash the awesome Rage technique to flatten your enemies - but watch out, bosses have their own to use on you! Speed running the old games? Improved AI is here to teach you a little humility. Ready for an even tougher challenge? Unlock Rebellion Mode and try to fight your way through as any member of the Streets of Rage cast. Finish a game with Galsia to prove you're the true SOR master! No one to play with? Grab an AI partner to keep you company.
Game.Title: Streets of Rage 2X
The King of Fighters Beat Em UP Plus

Game.Notes: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Red Sky Battle is a scrolling fighting game dedicated to the Ninja Turtles. It features 16-bit cartoon graphics with fluid animations and gameplay very similar to "Turtles in Time", the famous fighting game made by Konami in the 90s.
Game.Title: Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles: Red Sky Battle

Game.Notes: Command heroic knight Sir Arthur on a quest to defeat the forces of evil and save kindnaped princess Prin Prin. Scores of evil enemies awaits you , from zombies to gargoyles , ghosts to demons on your journey to save her. Will you survive the perils that lie in haunted countryside of demon world?

Game.Notes:
THE ULTIMATE GOLDEN AXE REMAKE!
* The original story revisited! * 7 characters from Golden Axe 1, 2 and 3 to choose from! * All characters have long/short range combos and custom throws, plus they can run, block, counter, and perform astonishing Special Moves! * Fill your magic meter and unleash the ultimate magic! * Find and ride the 4 different bizarrians, each with his own attack! * Enemies and bosses from Golden Axe 1, 2 and 3! Plus some surprises! * Choose your destiny, with multiple paths available! Will you find the path leading to the TRUE final battle? * Survival and training modes, where you can fight hordes of enemies and train your moves!
Game.Title: Golden Axe Legend

The game features a campaign starring Shadow Yamoto, one of the protagonists of Eternal Champions. It has several different features including:
* Alternative secret paths * 4 endings in the main campaign * 3 endings for extra modes * 3 unlockable modes * 5 unlockable characters
The game also features a rudimentary level up system, allowing the player to gain HP and MP, along with learning new combos and special skills.
